cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Structural Cognitive Emergence (SCE): Toward Structural Cognitive Runtime and Brain-Unit Intelligence"
message: "If you use this repository, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Tan"
    given-names: "Sizhe"
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
abstract: >
  Structural Cognitive Emergence (SCE) investigates how structural cognition may emerge from sparse examples,
  structural gaps, and developmental feedback rather than from brute-force memorization or purely black-box
  pattern fitting. The repository studies sparse concept formation, gap-driven why-question generation,
  in-situ structural knowledge growth, and a three-layer structural substrate built on Calling Graphs (CG),
  Differential Trees (DT), and Triggering Links (TL). This release extends SCE into its runtime phase through
  new work on Structural Cognitive Runtime (SCR), including runtime-oriented texts on three-cats reasoning,
  Gap/Why mechanisms, the twin of knowledge and mechanism, and a PRD for ASI Brain Units and Brain Unit Core.
  The repository now spans both structural cognitive emergence and its runtime extension toward brain-unit
  intelligence and LLM-hybrid structural cognitive systems.
keywords:
  - Structural Cognitive Emergence
  - Structural Cognitive Runtime
  - SCR
  - ASI Brain Units
  - Brain Unit Core
  - Sparse Concept Formation
  - Gap Why
  - Calling Graph
  - Differential Tree
  - Triggering Links
  - Developmental Learning
  - LLM Hybrid Runtime
